Loop to analyze all avi files in a specific folder
clear all
addpath(genpath(''))%Fill in path with all required functions (particle tracking function,
%trackprocessing,...)
allvdata = {};
alltrackdata = {};

Which folder?

%mkdir (['Auswertungsdateien\'], [filename '_Auswertung'])                        %creates the folder for the data
file = (['\']);       %creates the path to save the data, do not forget "\" at the end
file_ex = file;

addpath(genpath(file))
extension = '.avi';


%Add fps and Magnification or scale

fps = 40
Magnification = 63
scale = (5.86*2/Magnification) 
% scale = 0.19;                       %scalingfactor in micrometer/pixel

minlength = 10; %minimum tracklength in frames
vtresh = 200; %maximum velocity between two time steps in µm/s (tracks will be separated if larger)
Do all avi files in that folder
allfilenames = dir([file '*.avi']) %Finds all files ending on .avi
Loop over files from x to xmax
x = 1 %start with video 1
while(x <= length(allfilenames)) %Go until last video
    %try

Filename ending with a number (without the number)
    filename = allfilenames(x).name %Get filename of video
    filename = filename(1:end-4) %remove .avi from filename
Parameters for particle size - See https://de.mathworks.com/help/images/ref/regionprops.html
    MinLongAxis = 6;                    %parameters to select particles to track 
    MaxLongAxis = 35;                  %axis-parameters relate to an ellips with
    MinShortAxis = 6;                   %same second momentum
    MaxShortAxis = 35;                 %
    RatioMax = 2;                       %ratio of the two axis
    RatioMin = 1;                    %
    MinArea = 70;                       %Area of the detected particle
    MaxArea = 550;                      %
Parameters of tracks                                
    particle_numbering = 0;             %1 to produce Numberingvideo, 0 if not needed


    %constant_length = 0;                %0 if particle is nearly a square
                                        %length of the constant particlesite in
                                        %pixel if it is not a square

    CheckQuality = 3  ;                   %1 for quiver,2 for ellipse,3 for edge,0 for no checking - I recommend 3      
Important: Functions will load workspacevar --> make sure old tr is not loaded again! --> tr has to be deleted
    clear tr
    save('workspacevar');   
    mkdir ([file filename '_results'])

Which tasks should be carried out?
    % Call the function and capture the returned 'tr' variable
   
    [tr, RawResults, myangle, trajout] = particle_tracking_fct_angle2(filename, file);
trackdata = {};
    vdata = {};
    [trackdata,vdata] = track_processing(tr, vtresh, minlength, fps, scale); %process tracks to a cell array
   
trackdata: 1 = x in pixels, 2 = y in pixels, 3 = frame, 4 = orientation
vdata: 1-4 = differences from trackdata, 5 = speed in µm/s

Collect all trackdata and vdata from all videos in cell array
    alltrackdata = [alltrackdata,trackdata];
    allvdata = [allvdata,vdata];
 
    save([file filename '_results\' 'tracking.mat'],'tr', 'trackdata', 'vdata'); %save data for that video in one file 
    x=x+1; %go to next video 
end
save files with alltracks (combined tracks from all videos)
save([file mfilename '_alltrackings.mat'],'allvdata', 'alltrackdata');

